00:17:11,796 --> 00:17:14,657
Now as game developers, you might have had a lot of people ask you,

348
00:17:15,058 --> 00:17:16,858
oh, you're in games, what's that like?

349
00:17:17,839 --> 00:17:19,660
And of course the answer is, it depends.

350
00:17:20,440 --> 00:17:23,642
Working at a AAA studio is different from working at a bedroom indie,

351
00:17:23,682 --> 00:17:25,022
which is different from AAA,

352
00:17:25,503 --> 00:17:28,864
and even within the same class, like working at Valve is a very different

353
00:17:28,904 --> 00:17:30,905
experience from working at Blizzard, even though they're both AAA.

354
00:17:32,146 --> 00:17:38,948
And this is true of schools too. Each school will have a different emphasis on how they value teaching versus research versus service.

355
00:17:39,388 --> 00:17:41,909
Within each category, what kinds of things they look for.

356
00:17:42,409 --> 00:17:45,110
Every school has a different culture and a different community.

357
00:17:46,031 --> 00:17:51,753
And so, just like with game studios, everyone is different. You're not going to be happy at all of them.

358
00:17:52,453 --> 00:17:55,395
because there is a certain fit for your skills,

359
00:17:55,475 --> 00:17:57,476
for the types of things you want to do, for your culture.

360
00:17:57,937 --> 00:17:59,978
And so it's important to find places that are a good fit

361
00:18:00,018 --> 00:18:02,199
for your personal desires and strengths.

