00:28:08,363 --> 00:28:12,504
Probation in Canada at our college is one year, not six.

582
00:28:13,144 --> 00:28:16,685
So it's a little bit an easier slide.

583
00:28:17,545 --> 00:28:20,506
I wanted to ask you though, Ian, about the balance

584
00:28:20,546 --> 00:28:26,288
between work experience and academics.

585
00:28:27,008 --> 00:28:27,149
Yeah.

586
00:28:27,569 --> 00:28:28,990
It's, yeah.

587
00:28:29,030 --> 00:28:30,771
So it's usually on a sliding scale,

588
00:28:30,791 --> 00:28:32,352
but it varies widely by school.

589
00:28:32,392 --> 00:28:34,553
There are some schools that really, really

590
00:28:34,593 --> 00:28:36,874
want the academic credentials, and then the industry XP

591
00:28:36,894 --> 00:28:37,435
is a plus.

592
00:28:37,755 --> 00:28:39,536
There are some that are willing to sub-XP

593
00:28:39,616 --> 00:28:41,637
for academic credentials, depending

594
00:28:41,858 --> 00:28:43,158
on how much you have.

595
00:28:43,519 --> 00:28:44,879
If you're at the creative director,

596
00:28:45,160 --> 00:28:47,281
like director level position with 20 years industry

597
00:28:47,321 --> 00:28:49,942
experience, sometimes you can get along with just a bachelor's

598
00:28:50,022 --> 00:28:50,603
and it's fine.

599
00:28:51,804 --> 00:28:53,645
In the US, the reason it, the reason

600
00:28:53,825 --> 00:28:56,427
The way it works is it's not academic snobbery.

601
00:28:56,767 --> 00:29:00,591
It's that schools are beholden to their accreditation boards.

602
00:29:00,791 --> 00:29:02,132
Schools are accredited, which means

603
00:29:02,172 --> 00:29:05,054
that there's some outside, unbiased third party that

604
00:29:05,094 --> 00:29:07,036
looks at them and says, yes, you are actually

605
00:29:07,076 --> 00:29:08,377
teaching what you say you are.

606
00:29:09,298 --> 00:29:10,619
And you get the stamp of approval

607
00:29:10,679 --> 00:29:14,202
that basically gives them some legitimacy among students

608
00:29:14,342 --> 00:29:15,103
and everyone else.

609
00:29:17,505 --> 00:29:23,908
And the problem is that accreditation boards require you to have a certain percentage of

610
00:29:24,608 --> 00:29:26,949
faculty with advanced degrees.

611
00:29:27,270 --> 00:29:29,211
And so it's just kind of a non-starter for them.

612
00:29:29,631 --> 00:29:34,273
Now I will tell you that sufficient amounts of paperwork can make every problem go away.

613
00:29:35,014 --> 00:29:41,621
So if you are Will Wright and you want to teach and normally it requires a master's

614
00:29:41,661 --> 00:29:49,309
degree and you just have a bachelor's, the school can write enough stuff to their accreditation

615
00:29:49,329 --> 00:29:53,013
board to satisfy them to say this person is justified as qualified.

616
00:29:53,854 --> 00:29:56,575
The problem is that it's a lot of extra work.

617
00:29:56,695 --> 00:29:58,176
Academics don't have a whole lot of time.

618
00:29:58,256 --> 00:30:00,498
So for most people, they're not willing to do that.

619
00:30:00,518 --> 00:30:01,478
And they'll just tell you no.

620
00:30:02,239 --> 00:30:04,420
And really what they mean is, no, I don't have the time to

621
00:30:04,460 --> 00:30:04,881
deal with this.

